-- China Adds Financing Requirement for Industries, Securities Journal Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-14T22:36:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/china-adds-financing-requirement-for-industries-securities-journal-says.html
China will require companies in nine
industries to seek the “opinion” of the National Development
and Reform Commission for their fundraising plans, the China
Securities Journal reported, citing an unidentified person.  The requirement will be applied to companies in the steel,
cement, float glass, electrolytic aluminum, shipbuilding, coal
chemical, polysilicon, wind power equipment and large-scale
forging industries, according to the Beijing-based newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  